# React + TypeScript conventions

- Prefer **named exports** for reusable components and utilities; default export only for framework entrypoints when needed.
- Prefer `@/` imports over relative imports when crossing folders (especially across modules).
- Keep types close when module-specific; put shared types in `src/types/`.
- Keep UI primitives in `src/components/ui/`; put app-specific composed components in `src/components/` or in the owning module.
